'''Iorhael''' was a [[Sindarin]] name that [[Aragorn|Aragorn II]] used for [[Frodo Baggins]],<ref>{{HM|SD}} pp.129-31</ref> a translation of [[Westron]] name ''[[Maura]]''.
==Etymology==
The meaning is "old-wise" and comes from ''[[iaur]]'' and ''[[sael]]''.
